This paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems and techniques for improving their execution efficiency. This topic falls under the area of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and specifically constraint satisfaction and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of redundant modeling and channeling constraints, which are topics related to logic and verification (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper presents general theorems for proving propagation redundancy, which is a topic related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
